Instead of swallowing the `IOException`, you can wrap it into an `UncheckedIOException` and throw that.

In below code, method `findFiles` traverses the directory tree, starting at _dir_ and filters in regular files whose filename extension is `.java`

It then sorts the files by their size from largest to smallest.

It then collects the files to a `LinkedHashMap` where the [map] key is the path to the file and the [map] value is the size of the file. `LinkedHashMap` maintains the order in which entries are added to it. Since the entries are first sorted before adding them to the `LinkedHashMap`, the first entry is the file with the largest size.

Note that `LinkedHashMap` implements [interface] `SequencedMap` &amp;ndash; which was added in Java 21. `SequencedMap` declares method `firstEntry()` that returns the first entry which is the file with the largest size.

Finally, the method prints out the name and size of the largest file.
```java
import java.io.IOException;
import java.io.UncheckedIOException;
import java.nio.file.Files;
import java.nio.file.Path;
import java.nio.file.Paths;
import java.util.Comparator;
import java.util.LinkedHashMap;
import java.util.Map;
import java.util.SequencedMap;
import java.util.function.BinaryOperator;
import java.util.function.Function;
import java.util.function.Supplier;
import java.util.stream.Collectors;
import java.util.stream.Stream;

public class Greatest {

    private static void findFiles(Path dir, String ext) throws IOException {

        // Map key is path to the file.
        Function&lt;Path, Path&gt; keyMapper = path -&gt; path;

        // Map value is file size.
        Function&lt;Path, Long&gt; valueMapper = path -&gt; {
            try {
                return Files.size(path);
            }
            catch (IOException xIo) {
                throw new UncheckedIOException(xIo);
            }
        };

        // If two files have the same path (shouldn&#39;t occur), return the size
        // of the first file.
        BinaryOperator&lt;Long&gt; mergeFunction = (s1, s2) -&gt; s1;

        // Collect the stream elements into a &#39;LinkedHashMap&#39;
        Supplier&lt;Map&lt;Path, Long&gt;&gt; mapFactory = () -&gt; new LinkedHashMap&lt;Path, Long&gt;();

        try (Stream&lt;Path&gt; files = Files.walk(dir)) {
            System.out.println(((SequencedMap&lt;Path, Long&gt;) files.filter(p -&gt; Files.isRegularFile(p)  &amp;&amp;
                                                                        p.getFileName().toString().endsWith(ext))
                 .sorted(Comparator.comparing((Path p) -&gt; {
                     try {
                        return Files.size(p);
                    }
                    catch (IOException x) {
                        throw new UncheckedIOException(x);
                    }
                 }).reversed())
                 .collect(Collectors.toMap(keyMapper,
                                           valueMapper,
                                           mergeFunction,
                                           mapFactory))).firstEntry());
        };
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Path dir;
        if (args.length &gt; 0) {
            dir = Paths.get(args[0]);
        }
        else {
            dir = Paths.get(System.getProperty(&quot;user.dir&quot;));
        }
        String ext;
        if (args.length &gt; 1) {
            ext = args[1];
        }
        else {
            ext = &quot;.java&quot;;
        }
        try {
            findFiles(dir, ext);
        }
        catch (IOException xIo) {
            xIo.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
}
