1. Wake up in the morning
2. Eat breakfast
3. Go to school
4. Come back home 
5. Eat dinner 
6. Sleep

Sample data:
```
Transction Id   Event name       TimeStamp
 T1            Come back home      6 PM
 T1            Sleep               11 PM
 T2            Sleep               8 PM
 T2           Eat dinner           6 PM
 T3           Come back home       7 PM
 T3           Sleep                11 PM
 T4            Eat Dinner          6 PM
 T4            Sleep               8 PM  

Variant 1 -&gt;  (Come back home, Sleep) (T1, T3) so total count is 2
Variant 2 -&gt;   ( Eat dinner, Sleep) (T2, T4) so total 2 
```
Task is to find top 10 variants with maximum number of transactions

Current implementation:
```
1.Group events by transaction Id
2. Sort events for each transaction (Events for that transaction is sequenced)
3. Now concat event names for that transaction (ex for T1 Come back home, Sleep)
4. Do the same for each transaction. (Results are stored in hash table)
5. Count transactions with the same sequence ( Variants with counts) (Results are stored in hash table)
6. Find top 10 variants with highest transactions.
```
