I think I&#39;m getting what you intended to do. I encountered this as well in frames and panels a long time ago. This can be easily done in MVC approach.
Since you instantiated everything with default values in a parent frame or panel, no matter what you do in the child frame won&#39;t get updated if you call it from inside. You need to update the parent frame with revalidate and repaint methods, not the child. This is how it&#39;s done in frames and panels: Try it in a separate test scenario.

    parent.add(child); parent.setViewportView(child); parent.revalidate(); parent.repaint();

